Below is a clean end-to-end working example of an Aikau + Web Script + XHR flow.

⸻

🧩 Goal

On page load:

1. Aikau calls Alfresco Web Script
2. Web Script returns:

{ "message": "hello world" }

3. UI displays it in a label

⸻

1. 🔙 Web Script (Backend)

📁 Folder structure

alfresco/extension/templates/webscripts/com/example/demo/get-message.get.js
alfresco/extension/templates/webscripts/com/example/demo/get-message.get.desc.xml
alfresco/extension/templates/webscripts/com/example/demo/get-message.get.json.ftl

⸻

📄 Descriptor (.desc.xml)

<webscript>
  <shortname>Get Message</shortname>
  <description>Returns hello world JSON</description>
  <url>/com/example/demo/get-message</url>
  <format default="json">json</format>
  <authentication>user</authentication>
</webscript>

⸻

📄 Controller (.get.js)

model.message = "hello world";

⸻

📄 Response template (.json.ftl)

{
  "message": "${message}"
}

⸻

2. 🌐 Aikau Page (Frontend)

📁 Page definition (JS)

share/WEB-INF/classes/alfresco/site-webscripts/pages/demo-page.get.js

⸻

📄 Full Aikau page model

model.jsonModel = {
  services: [
    {
      name: "alfresco/services/Xhr"
    }
  ],
  widgets: [
    {
      name: "alfresco/layout/VerticalWidgets",
      config: {
        widgets: [
          {
            name: "alfresco/services/LoggingService"
          },
          {
            name: "alfresco/buttons/AlfButton",
            config: {
              label: "Load Message",
              publishTopic: "LOAD_MESSAGE"
            }
          },
          {
            name: "alfresco/html/Label",
            config: {
              label: "Waiting for response...",
              subscriptionTopic: "MESSAGE_RECEIVED",
              renderFilter: [
                {
                  property: "message",
                  values: [""],
                  negate: true
                }
              ]
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ]
};

⸻

3. 🔌 XHR Service Wiring

Now we wire the actual Web Script call.

Add this to services section OR page model widgets:

{
  name: "alfresco/services/Xhr",
  config: {
    subscriptions: [
      {
        topic: "LOAD_MESSAGE",
        url: "proxy/alfresco/com/example/demo/get-message",
        method: "GET",
        successTopic: "MESSAGE_RECEIVED"
      }
    ]
  }
}

⸻

4. 🔁 What happens (flow)

Step 1

User clicks button

LOAD_MESSAGE

Step 2

XHR service catches it

GET /share/proxy/alfresco/com/example/demo/get-message

Step 3

Response comes back:

{ "message": "hello world" }

Step 4

Aikau publishes:

MESSAGE_RECEIVED

Step 5

Label updates automatically

