Got it — you want the XHR call to fire automatically when the Aikau page loads, not via a button. That’s the correct production pattern.

In Aikau, you don’t “run code on load” directly in most OOTB widgets — you publish an event immediately when the page initializes.

Here’s the clean end-to-end way.

⸻

✅ Goal (on page load)

* Page loads
* XHR automatically calls Web Script
* Response is shown in label

⸻

🔥 1. Web Script (same as before)

Call it:

/share/proxy/alfresco/com/example/demo/get-message

Returns:

{ "message": "hello world" }

⸻

⚙️ 2. Aikau Page (AUTO LOAD VERSION)

This is the key part.

✅ Full page model

model.jsonModel = {
  services: [
    {
      name: "alfresco/services/Xhr",
      config: {
        subscriptions: [
          {
            topic: "PAGE_LOAD",
            url: "proxy/alfresco/com/example/demo/get-message",
            method: "GET",
            successTopic: "MESSAGE_RECEIVED"
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  widgets: [
    {
      name: "alfresco/layout/VerticalWidgets",
      config: {
        widgets: [
          {
            name: "alfresco/services/LoggingService"
          },
          // 👇 THIS triggers automatically on page load
          {
            name: "alfresco/services/PublishService",
            config: {
              publishTopic: "PAGE_LOAD"
            }
          },
          // 👇 UI display
          {
            name: "alfresco/html/Label",
            config: {
              label: "Loading...",
              subscriptionTopic: "MESSAGE_RECEIVED",
              renderFilter: [
                {
                  property: "message",
                  values: [""],
                  negate: true
                }
              ]
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ]
};

⸻

🧠 How it works (important)

1. Page loads

Aikau initializes all widgets

⸻

2. This runs immediately

PublishService → PAGE_LOAD

⸻

3. XHR service catches it

PAGE_LOAD → calls Web Script

⸻

4. Response comes back

{ "message": "hello world" }

⸻

5. Event published

MESSAGE_RECEIVED

⸻

6. Label updates automatically

⸻

⚠️ Key mistake people make

You were probably missing this piece:

❌ No automatic trigger exists unless you explicitly publish an event on load

Aikau is not React/Vue — there is no componentDidMount.

⸻

💡 Cleaner alternative (if you want BEST practice)

Instead of PublishService, you can also do:

Option A (recommended in real projects)

Use a tiny custom widget:

postCreate: function () {
   this.alfPublish("PAGE_LOAD");
}

⸻

Option B (OOTB only)

Use alfresco/services/PublishService (what I showed above)

⸻

🚀 If you still don’t see the call

Check in DevTools:

* Network tab → do you see /proxy/alfresco/...?
* Console → any Aikau topic errors?
* Confirm page model is actually loaded (wrong JS file is common issue)

